{"ID":270265, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"265\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs264.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs266.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 265<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">is no wonder He is so positive in the great declaration: He that believes and is baptized shall be\n  saved, and he that believes not shall be damned!<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> There was no other name given under heaven, nor\n  no other ordinance admitted, whereby men could be saved:<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> No wonder the Apostle said, being\n  &ldquo;buried with him in baptism,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> ye shall rise from the dead!<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> No wonder Paul had to arise and be\n  baptized and wash away his sins:<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> No wonder the angel told good old Cornelius that he must send\n  for Peter to learn how to be saved:<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> Peter could baptize,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> and angels could not, so long as there were\n  legal officers in the flesh<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> holding the keys of the kingdom,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> or the authority of the priesthood.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span>\n  There is one evidence still further on this point, and that is that Jesus himself when he appeared to\n  Paul on his way to Damascus,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> did not inform him how he could be saved.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> He had set in the\n  church first Apostles, and secondly prophets, for the work of the ministry, perfecting of the saints,<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span>\n  etc.; and as the grand rule of heaven<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> was that nothing should ever be done on earth without\n  revealing the secret to his servants the prophets, agreeably to Amos 3:7,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> so Paul could not learn\n  so much from the Lord relative to his duty in the common salvation<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> of man, as he could from one\n  of Christ&rsquo;s ambassadors<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> called with the same heavenly calling<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> of the Lord, and endowed with the\n  same power from on high<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span>&mdash;so that what they loosed on earth, should be loosed in heaven; and\n  what they bound on earth should be bound in heaven:<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> He, the Lord being a priest forever, after the\n  order of Melchizedek,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> and the anointed Son of God,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> from before the foundation of the world,<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span>\n  and they be begotten sons of Jesus<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> through the gospel, to teach all nations&mdash;and lo I am with you\n  always to the end of the world<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span>&mdash;that is&mdash;by the other comforter which the world cannot\n  receive<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span>&mdash;for ye are the witnesses<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span>&mdash;having the testimony of Jesus which is the spirit of\n  prophecy.<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Necessity of Repentance<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">From what has already been introduced as testimony to prove that no man can be saved without\n  baptism,<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span> it will be seen and acknowledged that if there was sin among men, repentance was as\n  necessary at one time<span class=\"footRef\">30<\/span> or age of the world as another&mdash;and that other foundation can no man lay\n  than that is laid, which is Jesus Christ.<span class=\"footRef\">31<\/span> If, then, Abel was a righteous man<span class=\"footRef\">32<\/span> he had to become so\n  by keeping the commandments; if<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108381\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108381)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108381)\">Mark 16:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114719\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114719)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114719)\">D&amp;C 84:74<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108987\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108987)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108987)\">Acts 4:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111232\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111232)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111232)\">2 Ne. 31:21<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109273\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109273)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109273)\">Rom. 6:4<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109908\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109908)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109908)\">Col. 2:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116144\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116144)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116144)\">D&amp;C 128:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109053\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109053)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109053)\">Acts 9:6,18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109191\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109191)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109191)\">Acts 22:16<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109057\"><a href=\"javascript:vo